  introLines:
  - Package for... wait. This isn't the hospital roof
  - My legs finally stopped burning. That's a good sign, right?
  answerWhatHappenedBefore: The hospital elevators failed during a blackout. I had
    a cooler with a donor heart. I ran up every single flight of stairs, handed it
    to the surgeon, and my lungs just collapsed
  answerWhatKindOfLife: I just delivered boxes. Nothing fancy. I always made sure
    people got what they ordered, no matter what
  answerWhatWasYourJob: I literally ran up fifty flights of concrete stairs carrying
    heavy gear. I am drenched in sweat and covered in dust from the stairwell
  answerWhatHappenedClothes: I literally ran up fifty flights of concrete stairs
    carrying heavy gear. I am drenched in sweat and covered in dust from the stairwell
  answerWhyHaveItem: This medical bag contains the temperature-controlled delivery
    pod. It saved a life today, so please handle it with care
